    <theorem xml:id="th_inverse_trig_derivative">
        <title>Derivatives of inverse trig functions</title>
      <statement>
        <p>
          The following derivative/antiderivative formulas hold:
          <md>
            <mrow>\frac{d}{dx} \arcsin x=\frac{1}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}\amp \iff \int \frac{1}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}\, dx=\arcsin x+C \amp \text{ (for all \(x\) in \((-1,1)\)) }</mrow>
            <mrow>\frac{d}{dx} \arccos x=-\frac{1}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}\amp \iff \int \frac{1}{\sqrt{1-x^2}}\, dx=-\arccos x+C \amp \text{ (for all \(x\) in \((-1,1)\)) }</mrow>
            <mrow>\frac{d}{dx} \arctan x=\frac{1}{1+x^2}\amp \iff \int \frac{1}{1+x^2}\, dx=\arctan x+C \amp \text{ (for all \(x\)) } </mrow>
          </md>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </theorem>
